JOHANNESBURG The ANC will hold its national executive committee meeting on Monday with details of the agenda yet to be revealed.The meeting comes as events unfold following the State of the Nation debate two weeks ago.Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan is set to deliver his budget speech in parliament on Wednesday amid speculation about his future.Former Eskom CEO Brian Molefe will be sworn in as a member of parliament this week.READ: ANC NEC members shouldn't be in government: branchOpposition parties and analysts have criticised the appointment, with many predicting Molefe could replace Gordhan as head of treasury.Last week, the ANC Youth League called for Gordhan to be axed saying he and his top management have failed in their duties. We are fully behind our Minister of Finance. He was appointed by President Zuma himself. And doing an excellent job! https://t.co/T9iXnYyun0 Treasury has however tweeted that its leaders remain resolute and ready to deliver the budget speech on Wednesday. The Minister of Finance, Mr Pravin Gordhan, will deliver the Budget Speech on Wed 22 February at 2pm https://t.co/leCQeUDrhd #Budget2017 pic.twitter.com/S7G3Luvu7Q Former ANC treasurer-general Mathews Phosa on Sunday called on President Jacob Zuma to step down.READ: ANC: As NEC outlines 2017 plans, controversies remain unaddressedIn an opinion piece, Phosa said the entire governing party s NEC should be dissolved.The former Mpumalanga premier said the party doesn t serve the people who voted it into power.The ANC is set to hold a policy conference in June, culminating with an elective conference in December where the party is set to elect Zuma s successor. eNCA